<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="890" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Moore</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-29"><hi rend="italic">April 29,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 593.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I append on the overleaf copy of the
                            Department’s telegram of the 27th instant, directing you to communicate
                            to the Persian minister at London official information of the
                            proclamation of war with Spain.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                    Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg></opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-27"><hi rend="italic">April 27,
                                        1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Communicate to Persian minister in London official information of
                                proclamation of existing state of war with Spain in order that his
                                Government may be advised.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>